{"copyright": {"licenseType": "NO", "determinationType": "OTHER", "thirdPartyContentCondition": "NOT_SET"}, "subjectCategories": ["GEOPHYSICS"], "exportControl": {"isExportControl": "NO", "ear": "NO", "itar": "NO"}, "created": "2013-08-08T15:57:00.0000000+00:00", "distributionDate": "2019-06-20T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "center": {"code": "CDMS", "name": "Legacy CDMS", "id": "092d6e0881874968859b972d39a888dc"}, "onlyAbstract": false, "sensitiveInformation": 2, "fundingNumbers": [{"number": "NSG-7102", "type": "CONTRACT_GRANT"}, {"number": "NGR-05-009-110", "type": "CONTRACT_GRANT"}, {"number": "NSF MPS-74-21195", "type": "CONTRACT_GRANT"}, {"number": "NSF MPS-74-23501", "type": "CONTRACT_GRANT"}], "abstract": "The concepts of 'frozen-in magnetic field lines' and 'field-line reconnection', which are frequently used in discussions of the theory of the magnetosphere, have been criticized by Alfven and Falthammar (1971), by Heikkila (1973), and by Alfven (1975). In the present paper, it is demonstrated that both concepts are unnecessary and often misleading. The frozen-in concept is shown to belong to the pseudo-plasma formalism which is useful only in special cases.", "title": "On frozen-in field lines and field-line reconnection", "stiType": "REPRINT", "distribution": "PUBLIC", "submittedDate": "2013-08-08T15:57:00.0000000+00:00", "isLessonsLearned": false, "authorAffiliations": [{"sequence": 0, "submissionId": 19760059748, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Alfven, H."}, "organization": {"name": "California, University", "location": "La Jolla, Calif., United States"}}, "id": "7455d2ab91ed44ddbd8639d47e979768"}], "disseminated": "METADATA_ONLY", "stiTypeDetails": "Reprint (Version printed in journal)", "technicalReviewType": "TECHNICAL_REVIEW_TYPE_NONE", "modified": "2011-08-15T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "id": 19760059748, "publications": [{"volume": "81", "submissionId": 19760059748, "id": "c59bdd41596c4650ad8430fd77abbfd7", "publicationName": "Journal of Geophysical Research", "publicationDate": "1976-08-01T00:00:00.0000000+00:00"}], "status": "CURATED", "related": [], "downloads": [], "downloadsAvailable": false, "index": "submissions-2022-09-30-06-07"}